summary:
Experienced journalist who believes in the power of words to inform, inspire, and drive positive change. Currently pursuing a Master's degree in English Language and Culture building upon a solid foundation in English Studies. My academic education has equipped me with a comprehensive understanding of literary analysis and the nuances of effective communication.

Over the past four years, I have been actively involved in journalism, honing my skills in research, interviewing, and storytelling. I have produced compelling features in an array of topics with a strong focus on human rights topics, including LGBTQIA+ rights, elderly care, migrant communities, and mental health advocacy. By amplifying marginalised voices and sharing their stories, I strive to foster empathy and create a more inclusive society.
